iSo there are a billion forms of divination out there, but why? Do		gopher.black	70
ithey all work? Do any of them work? How do they purport to work?		gopher.black	70
iLets focus on the last bit first. How does divination work? This		gopher.black	70
iis the interesting bit for me at least.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
iIn cleromancy the mechanism of action is some sort of randomness.		gopher.black	70
iCleromancy is about "tossing stuff" like dice and seeing what		gopher.black	70
icomes up. Some practitioners suggest that the randomness allows		gopher.black	70
ithe supernatural to take direct action and influence the results		gopher.black	70
iof the toss. Other practitioners would say that the toss and its		gopher.black	70
irandomness is just that and not influenced by the supernatural,		gopher.black	70
ibut the querent (person seeking information) must use their		gopher.black	70
iintuition to understand the results of the toss. That type of		gopher.black	70
ipractitioner moves the supernatural action internal to the		gopher.black	70
iunconscious mind and changes its domain of action to the		gopher.black	70
iinterpretation alone. But there are still other types! Some see		gopher.black	70
ithe unconscious mind as affecting the toss itself in a sort of		gopher.black	70
iblend of the first two. Others shy away from intuition and suggest		gopher.black	70
iself-reflection and psychology allow the interpretation of any		gopher.black	70
isymbol to be helpful as a means of thinking in a new way about the		gopher.black	70
iissue.		gopher.black	70
i		gopher.black	70
